255
00:21:51,102 --> 00:21:53,980
- Clarice, phone. It's the guru.
- Crawford?

256
00:21:54,064 --> 00:21:55,148
- Yeah.
- Thanks, Ardelia.

257
00:21:55,690 --> 00:21:57,317
- Starling?
- <i>Sir?</i>

258
00:21:58,318 --> 00:21:59,778
Miggs is dead.

259
00:22:00,904 --> 00:22:03,532
Dead? How?

260
00:22:04,491 --> 00:22:07,994
The orderly heard Lecter whispering
to him all afternoon, and Miggs crying.

261
00:22:08,078 --> 00:22:11,748
They found him at bed check.
He'd swallowed his own tongue.

262
00:22:13,625 --> 00:22:14,918
Starling?

263
00:22:15,293 --> 00:22:17,254
Yeah, I'm still here, sir.

264
00:22:17,337 --> 00:22:20,298
I just... I don't know
how to feel about this.

265
00:22:20,799 --> 00:22:25,095
You don't have to feel any way about it.
Lecter did it to amuse himself.

266
00:22:25,554 --> 00:22:27,847
<i>Look, I know it got ugly today,</i>

267
00:22:28,056 --> 00:22:31,309
but you mentioned a name
at the end. Mofet.

268
00:22:31,476 --> 00:22:33,228
Any follow-up on her?

269
00:22:33,979 --> 00:22:36,773
Well, Lecter altered or destroyed
most of his patients' histories

270
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:39,401
prior to capture, so there's no record
of anyone named Mofet.

271
00:22:39,484 --> 00:22:43,738
But I thought the "yourself' reference

272
00:22:43,822 --> 00:22:45,407
was too hokey for Lecter,

273
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:49,744
so I figured, he's from Baltimore,
and I looked in the phone book,

274
00:22:49,828 --> 00:22:53,331
and there's a "Your Self Storage" facility,

275
00:22:53,415 --> 00:22:55,667
<i>right outside of downtown Baltimore, sir.</i>

276
00:22:57,961 --> 00:23:01,756
Unit 31 was leased for 10 years,

277
00:23:02,007 --> 00:23:03,550
prepaid in full.

278
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,051
The contract

279
00:23:05,135 --> 00:23:09,180
is in the name of a Miss Hester Mofet.

280
00:23:10,015 --> 00:23:12,517
So nobody's been in here since 1980?

281
00:23:12,809 --> 00:23:14,561
Not to my knowledge.

282
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:19,107
Privacy is a great concern
to my customers.

283
00:23:19,691 --> 00:23:21,901
Yes, I won't disturb anything. I promise.

284
00:23:21,985 --> 00:23:24,446
I'll be out of here before you know it.

285
00:23:24,529 --> 00:23:28,116
- Can I help you?
- Yes, actually, you can.

286
00:23:33,204 --> 00:23:34,456
It's stuck.

287
00:23:34,539 --> 00:23:37,292
We could return tomorrow with my son.

288
00:23:37,542 --> 00:23:39,044
What about him?

289
00:23:40,378 --> 00:23:45,133
I would ask my driver to help you,
but he detests physical labor.

290
00:23:46,051 --> 00:23:47,218
Great.

291
00:23:47,802 --> 00:23:50,805
You just stay here.
I'll be back in one minute.

292
00:24:23,046 --> 00:24:24,339
It's stuck.

293
00:24:24,422 --> 00:24:26,508
Hand me that flashlight, sir.

294
00:24:37,185 --> 00:24:38,269
Oh.

295
00:24:40,105 --> 00:24:44,442
If this door should fall down
or anything else,

296
00:24:45,985 --> 00:24:48,863
this is the number
for our Baltimore field office.

297
00:24:48,947 --> 00:24:50,740
Now, they know that you're with me.

298
00:24:50,824 --> 00:24:52,867
You call them if anything should happen.

299
00:24:52,951 --> 00:24:54,619
Yes, Miss Starling.

300
00:27:25,728 --> 00:27:26,729
Clarice...

301
00:27:27,313 --> 00:27:30,275
- They're waiting for you. Watch yourself.
- Thank you.

302
00:27:31,192 --> 00:27:34,487
Hester Mofet.
It's an anagram, isn't it, Doctor?

303
00:27:35,446 --> 00:27:38,700
Hester Mofet, "The rest of me."

304
00:27:38,783 --> 00:27:42,453
"Miss The Rest Of Me,"
meaning that you rented that garage?

305
00:28:18,615 --> 00:28:19,908
Thank you.

306
00:28:20,491 --> 00:28:22,493
Your bleeding has stopped.

307
00:28:24,621 --> 00:28:26,122
How did you...

308
00:28:27,832 --> 00:28:29,250
It's nothing.

309
00:28:29,667 --> 00:28:31,336
It's just a scratch.

310
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:35,048
Dr. Lecter, whose head is in that bottle?

311
00:28:35,131 --> 00:28:38,301
Why don't you ask me about Buffalo Bill?

312
00:28:38,468 --> 00:28:40,386
Why, do you know something about him?

313
00:28:40,470 --> 00:28:42,597
I might, if I saw the case file.

314
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,599
You could get that for me.

315
00:28:44,682 --> 00:28:46,309
Why don't we talk about Miss Mofet?

316
00:28:46,392 --> 00:28:48,353
You wanted me to find him.

317
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:51,981
His real name is Benjamin Raspail.

318
00:28:52,523 --> 00:28:54,275
A former patient of mine,

319
00:28:54,359 --> 00:28:58,821
whose romantic attachments ran to,
shall we say, the exotic.

320
00:28:59,489 --> 00:29:00,990
I did not kill him, I assure you.

321
00:29:01,074 --> 00:29:03,785
Merely tucked him away
very much as I found him,

322
00:29:03,868 --> 00:29:06,371
after he'd missed three appointments.

323
00:29:07,538 --> 00:29:09,874
If you didn't kill him, then who did, sir?

324
00:29:09,958 --> 00:29:11,250
Who can say?

325
00:29:11,334 --> 00:29:13,002
Best thing for him, really.

326
00:29:13,086 --> 00:29:15,296
His therapy was going nowhere.

327
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:18,841
His dress, makeup...

328
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:21,302
Raspail was a transvestite?

329
00:29:21,386 --> 00:29:23,763
In life? Oh, no.

330
00:29:23,846 --> 00:29:26,140
Garden variety manic-depressive.

331
00:29:26,224 --> 00:29:28,309
Tedious. Very tedious.

332
00:29:28,893 --> 00:29:31,437
And I just think of him
as a kind of experiment,

333
00:29:31,521 --> 00:29:34,899
a fledgling killer's first effort
at transformation.

334
00:29:35,108 --> 00:29:37,860
How did you feel
when you saw him, Clarice?

335
00:29:38,444 --> 00:29:40,363
Scared at first, then,

336
00:29:41,364 --> 00:29:42,740
exhilarated.

337
00:29:43,324 --> 00:29:45,660
Jack Crawford is helping your career,
isn't he?

338
00:29:45,743 --> 00:29:48,788
Apparently, he likes you,
and you like him, too.

339
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:51,082
I never thought about it.

340
00:29:51,374 --> 00:29:54,335
Do you think Jack Crawford
wants you sexually?

341
00:29:54,419 --> 00:29:55,962
True, he is much older,

342
00:29:56,045 --> 00:29:59,674
but do you think he visualizes
scenarios, exchanges,

343
00:29:59,757 --> 00:30:01,092
fucking you?

344
00:30:03,928 --> 00:30:05,346
That doesn't interest me, Doctor.

345
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:09,017
Frankly, it's the sort of thing
that Miggs would say.

346
00:30:10,977 --> 00:30:12,395
Not anymore.

347
00:30:20,153 --> 00:30:21,738
Thank you, Barney.

348
00:30:25,742 --> 00:30:27,994
What happened to your drawings?

349
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:31,622
Punishment, you see, for Miggs.

350
00:30:32,081 --> 00:30:33,958
Just like that gospel program.

351
00:30:34,042 --> 00:30:37,086
When you leave,
they'll turn the volume way up.

352
00:30:37,170 --> 00:30:40,214
Dr. Chilton does enjoy his petty torments.

353
00:30:41,049 --> 00:30:43,885
What did you mean
by transformation, Doctor?

354
00:30:52,477 --> 00:30:55,772
I've been in this room
for eight years now, Clarice.

355
00:30:56,230 --> 00:30:59,650
I know they will never,
ever let me out while I'm alive.

356
00:31:00,485 --> 00:31:02,278
What I want is a view.

357
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:06,657
I want a window where I can see a tree,
or even water.

358
00:31:06,824 --> 00:31:10,286
I want to be in a federal institution
far away from Dr. Chilton.

359
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:12,914
What did you mean by fledgling killer?

360
00:31:13,206 --> 00:31:15,249
Are you saying that he's killed again?

361
00:31:15,333 --> 00:31:18,628
I'm offering you a psychological profile
on Buffalo Bill,

362
00:31:18,711 --> 00:31:20,755
based on the case evidence.

363
00:31:26,219 --> 00:31:28,596
I'll help you catch him, Clarice.

364
00:31:35,353 --> 00:31:37,480
You know who he is, don't you?

365
00:31:38,356 --> 00:31:41,150
Tell me who decapitated
your patient, Doctor.

366
00:31:41,234 --> 00:31:43,945
All good things to those who wait.

367
00:31:44,529 --> 00:31:45,780
I've waited, Clarice,

368
00:31:45,863 --> 00:31:48,699
but how long can you
and old Jackie boy wait?

369
00:31:49,158 --> 00:31:51,119
Our little Billy must already be searching

370
00:31:51,202 --> 00:31:54,163
for that next special lady.

371
00:32:57,602 --> 00:32:59,312
Hey, little cheeper.

372
00:33:08,029 --> 00:33:09,739
I'll be right there.

373
00:33:10,531 --> 00:33:11,699
Oh, shoot.

374
00:33:18,748 --> 00:33:19,999
Goddamn it.

375
00:33:29,175 --> 00:33:30,635
Perfect! Jesus.

376
00:33:36,474 --> 00:33:38,226
Can I help you with that?

377
00:33:39,310 --> 00:33:41,354
- Would you?
- Sure.

378
00:33:42,438 --> 00:33:44,106
- Thank you.
- That's all right.

379
00:33:44,190 --> 00:33:46,567
- You look kind of handicapped.
- Yeah.

380
00:33:46,901 --> 00:33:49,904
I got it this far.
I just can't get it up in the truck.

381
00:33:49,987 --> 00:33:51,489
Here. Just grab this.

382
00:33:52,031 --> 00:33:53,074
Okay.

383
00:33:53,157 --> 00:33:55,326
Good. Just set it down. That's good.

384
00:33:56,035 --> 00:33:59,330
Get in the truck.
I want to push it all the way up.

385
00:34:00,039 --> 00:34:02,041
- I really appreciate this. Thank you.
- All right.

386
00:34:02,124 --> 00:34:03,709
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

387
00:34:04,335 --> 00:34:06,295
Just go all the way back.

388
00:34:07,129 --> 00:34:08,965
Okay. Is this good?

389
00:34:09,048 --> 00:34:10,549
Yeah, that's good.

390
00:34:12,426 --> 00:34:14,595
- That's great.
- Okay.

391
00:34:15,096 --> 00:34:17,431
Say, are you about a size 14?

392
00:34:17,682 --> 00:34:18,766
Sorry?

393
00:34:40,162 --> 00:34:41,205
Good.

394
00:34:59,557 --> 00:35:03,311
Oh, good. Good.

395
00:35:19,285 --> 00:35:20,411
Hold!

396
00:35:33,007 --> 00:35:34,216
Starling!

397
00:35:36,927 --> 00:35:38,637
Outside. Let's go.

398
00:35:39,847 --> 00:35:42,725
Cindy, in the ring for Starling. Let's go!

399
00:35:51,108 --> 00:35:52,985
FBI! Hold it! Hold it right there!

400
00:35:53,069 --> 00:35:54,779
Saddle up. Pack your field gear.
You're moving out.

401
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:56,280
- You're going with Crawford.
- Where?

402
00:35:56,364 --> 00:35:58,074
Found a girl's body down in West Virginia.

403
00:35:58,157 --> 00:36:00,785
Been in the water about a week.
Looks like a Buffalo Bill-type situation.

404
00:36:13,005 --> 00:36:16,133
He keeps them alive for three days.
We don't know why.

405
00:36:16,217 --> 00:36:19,387
There's no evidence
of rape or physical abuse prior to death.

406
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:22,473
All the mutilation you see there
is postmortem.

407
00:36:22,848 --> 00:36:24,517
Okay, three days.

408
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:28,270
Then he shoots them, skins them,
and dumps them.

409
00:36:28,562 --> 00:36:30,356
Each body in a different river.

410
00:36:30,439 --> 00:36:33,609
The water leaves us no trace evidence
of any kind.

411
00:36:33,692 --> 00:36:36,320
That's Fredrica Bimmel, the first one.

412
00:36:36,404 --> 00:36:39,407
Her body was the only one
he took the trouble to weight down,

413
00:36:39,490 --> 00:36:42,201
so actually, she was the third girl found.

414
00:36:42,493 --> 00:36:44,328
After her, he got lazy.

415
00:36:46,664 --> 00:36:49,125
Okay. Let's see.

416
00:36:49,792 --> 00:36:51,752
Circles where the girls were abducted,

417
00:36:51,836 --> 00:36:54,130
arrows where their bodies were found.

418
00:36:54,213 --> 00:36:57,383
This new one today washed up here.

419
00:36:57,466 --> 00:36:58,926
Elk River, West Virginia.

420
00:37:18,612 --> 00:37:21,490
Look at him, Starling.
Tell me what you see.

421
00:37:22,450 --> 00:37:23,993
Well, he's a white male.

422
00:37:24,076 --> 00:37:27,746
Serial killers tend to hunt
within their own ethnic groups.

423
00:37:27,830 --> 00:37:28,873
He's not a drifter.

424
00:37:28,956 --> 00:37:32,501
He's got his own house somewhere,
not an apartment.

425
00:37:32,835 --> 00:37:35,838
- Why?
- What he does with them takes privacy.

426
00:37:36,380 --> 00:37:38,382
He's in his 30s or 40s.

427
00:37:38,466 --> 00:37:40,759
He's got real physical strength,

428
00:37:41,010 --> 00:37:43,846
combined with an older man's self-control.

429
00:37:43,929 --> 00:37:46,182
He's cautious, precise.

430
00:37:47,016 --> 00:37:49,852
And he's never impulsive. He'll never stop.

431
00:37:50,227 --> 00:37:51,479
Why not?

432
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:56,692
He's got a real taste for it now.
He's getting better at his work.

433
00:37:58,277 --> 00:38:00,029
Not bad, Starling.

434
00:38:00,112 --> 00:38:02,406
- Questions?
- Yes, sir.

435
00:38:03,282 --> 00:38:06,827
You haven't mentioned anything about
the information contained in my report

436
00:38:06,911 --> 00:38:09,038
or Dr. Lecter's offer, sir.

437
00:38:09,121 --> 00:38:10,915
I'm considering it.

438
00:38:11,081 --> 00:38:13,918
That's why you sent me in there, isn't it?

439
00:38:14,001 --> 00:38:16,170
To get his help on Buffalo Bill, sir?

440
00:38:19,215 --> 00:38:22,092
Well, if that was the case, then I just...

441
00:38:22,426 --> 00:38:24,845
I just wish I was in on it. That's all.

442
00:38:25,095 --> 00:38:27,389
If I had sent you in there
with an actual agenda,

443
00:38:27,473 --> 00:38:29,350
Lecter would have known it instantly.

444
00:38:29,433 --> 00:38:32,728
He would have toyed with you,
then turned to stone.

445
00:39:06,428 --> 00:39:09,807
Excuse me.
Sheriff Perkins, these are the FBI people.

446
00:39:09,974 --> 00:39:12,518
Sheriff Perkins. Jack Crawford, FBI.

447
00:39:12,851 --> 00:39:15,437
Special Agent Terry, Agent Starling.

448
00:39:15,646 --> 00:39:18,107
We appreciate being invited
to your jurisdiction.

449
00:39:18,190 --> 00:39:21,485
I didn't call you. That was somebody
from the State Attorney's office.

450
00:39:21,569 --> 00:39:23,737
We'll extend you every courtesy,
but right now...

451
00:39:23,821 --> 00:39:28,242
Sheriff, this type of sex crime
has certain aspects.

452
00:39:28,325 --> 00:39:30,619
I'd just as soon discuss in private.

453
00:39:30,703 --> 00:39:32,496
You know what I mean?

454
00:41:23,190 --> 00:41:25,776
- Oscar, fetch Dr. Akin from the chapel.
- Yes, sir.

455
00:41:25,859 --> 00:41:27,069
Starling, we're back here.

456
00:41:27,152 --> 00:41:29,822
Tell Lamar to come on
when he's finished playing his music.

457
00:41:30,447 --> 00:41:32,991
Yeah. We'll be sending in a minute.

458
00:41:33,784 --> 00:41:34,952
Is this working?

459
00:41:35,035 --> 00:41:37,705
I need a six-way linkup.

460
00:41:37,788 --> 00:41:39,498
Chicago, Detroit...

461
00:41:39,581 --> 00:41:40,958
What? What?

462
00:41:46,171 --> 00:41:48,882
Excuse me! Excuse me, gentlemen.

463
00:41:48,966 --> 00:41:51,218
You officers and gentlemen,
listen here now.

464
00:41:51,301 --> 00:41:52,886
There's things we need to do for her.

465
00:41:52,970 --> 00:41:54,805
I know that you all brought her this far

466
00:41:54,888 --> 00:41:57,558
and that her folks would
thank you if they could

467
00:41:57,641 --> 00:41:59,893
for your kindness and your sensitivity.

468
00:41:59,977 --> 00:42:03,480
And now, please,
go on now and let us take care of her.

469
00:42:04,189 --> 00:42:05,566
Go on, now.

470
00:42:08,652 --> 00:42:09,987
Thank you.

471
00:42:13,699 --> 00:42:15,075
Thank you.

472
00:42:16,827 --> 00:42:18,245
Okay, good.

473
00:42:26,503 --> 00:42:29,214
Yeah, that's right. West Virginia. Elk River.

474
00:42:29,298 --> 00:42:31,341
Stand by for transmission.

475
00:42:35,179 --> 00:42:36,305
Ray.

476
00:42:48,734 --> 00:42:51,487
Doctor, Lamar, let's take a look at her.

477
00:43:08,003 --> 00:43:09,338
Oh, Jesus.

478
00:43:17,095 --> 00:43:18,680
Okay, Starling.

479
00:43:23,727 --> 00:43:24,853
Bill.

480
00:43:40,911 --> 00:43:45,374
Star-shaped contact entrance wound
over the sternum.

481
00:43:47,584 --> 00:43:49,670
Muzzle stamp at the top.

482
00:43:49,753 --> 00:43:52,214
- Wrongful death.
- "Wrongful death."

483
00:43:53,090 --> 00:43:56,426
She'll have to go
to the state pathologist at Claxton.

484
00:43:56,510 --> 00:43:58,804
Well, I better get back to that service.

485
00:43:58,887 --> 00:44:00,639
Lamar will help you.

486
00:44:00,931 --> 00:44:02,474
Lord Almighty.

487
00:44:06,937 --> 00:44:09,273
What else do you see, Starling?

488
00:44:10,232 --> 00:44:12,526
Well, she's not local.

489
00:44:13,819 --> 00:44:16,947
Her ears are pierced three times,
and there's...

490
00:44:18,198 --> 00:44:21,285
Glitter nail polish. It looks like town to me.

491
00:44:26,957 --> 00:44:28,667
Two of her fingernails are broken off,

492
00:44:28,750 --> 00:44:32,296
and there's dirt or grit under them.

493
00:44:32,963 --> 00:44:36,550
It looks like she's tried to claw her way
through something.

494
00:44:36,633 --> 00:44:39,428
Ray, get pictures of her teeth.
We'll fax them through Missing Persons.

495
00:44:39,511 --> 00:44:40,679
Right.

496
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:52,149
Let's do another.

497
00:45:00,908 --> 00:45:03,368
She's got something in her throat.

498
00:45:03,911 --> 00:45:05,787
When a body comes out of the water,

499
00:45:05,871 --> 00:45:08,999
lots of times there's, like,
leaves and things in the mouth.

500
00:45:40,197 --> 00:45:43,033
What is that, some kind of seedpod?

501
00:45:43,825 --> 00:45:46,244
No, sir. That's a bug cocoon.

502
00:45:46,912 --> 00:45:49,748
There's no way that could get
way down in there like that.

503
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:52,542
Not unless somebody shoved it in there.

504
00:45:54,836 --> 00:45:57,381
She'll be easier to print
when we turn her over.

505
00:45:57,464 --> 00:46:00,759
- Lamar, will you give me a hand with this?
- Yes, sir, I will.

506
00:46:04,554 --> 00:46:08,100
Oh, Jack. What do you make of these?

507
00:46:08,558 --> 00:46:10,644
Different configuration
than the other victims.

508
00:46:10,727 --> 00:46:11,979
