01:01:20,970 --> 01:01:22,972
Paul Krendler's over here from Justice.

749
01:01:23,055 --> 01:01:25,558
She's asking him to take over in Memphis.

750
01:01:50,541 --> 01:01:52,293
Welcome to Memphis, Dr. Lecter.

751
01:01:52,376 --> 01:01:55,171
I'm Lieutenant Boyle.
This is Sergeant Patrick.

752
01:01:55,254 --> 01:01:57,423
Now, we're gonna treat you
as good as you treat us.

753
01:01:57,506 --> 01:02:01,010
You be a gentleman,
you gonna get three hots and a cot.

754
01:02:01,761 --> 01:02:05,222
Sir. If you sign right here,
we'll have us a legal transfer.

755
01:02:08,309 --> 01:02:09,727
Where is it?

756
01:02:10,978 --> 01:02:12,772
Here, sir. Use mine.

757
01:02:59,860 --> 01:03:03,739
Senator Martin, Dr. Hannibal Lecter.

758
01:03:09,036 --> 01:03:10,413
Dr. Lecter,

759
01:03:11,080 --> 01:03:14,417
I brought an affidavit
guaranteeing your new rights.

760
01:03:14,750 --> 01:03:17,420
You'll want to read it before I sign.

761
01:03:20,923 --> 01:03:25,344
I won't waste your time or Catherine's
time bargaining for petty privileges.

762
01:03:25,428 --> 01:03:27,513
Clarice Starling
and that awful Jack Crawford

763
01:03:27,596 --> 01:03:29,682
have wasted far too much time already.

764
01:03:29,765 --> 01:03:32,810
I only pray they haven't doomed
the poor girl.

765
01:03:33,936 --> 01:03:37,523
Let me help you now
and I will trust you when it is all over.

766
01:03:37,606 --> 01:03:39,567
You have my word. Paul?

767
01:03:42,069 --> 01:03:44,905
Buffalo Bill's real name is Louis Friend.

768
01:03:46,157 --> 01:03:47,199
I met him just once.

769
01:03:47,283 --> 01:03:50,369
He was referred to me in April
or May, 1980,

770
01:03:50,453 --> 01:03:52,788
by my patient Benjamin Raspail.

771
01:03:53,289 --> 01:03:55,374
They were lovers, you see.

772
01:03:55,541 --> 01:03:58,961
But Raspail had become very frightened.

773
01:03:59,795 --> 01:04:02,965
Apparently, Louis had murdered
a transient

774
01:04:03,424 --> 01:04:06,510
and done things with her skin.

775
01:04:07,553 --> 01:04:10,639
We need his address
and a physical description.

776
01:04:11,640 --> 01:04:13,309
Tell me, Senator.

777
01:04:13,976 --> 01:04:16,395
Did you nurse Catherine yourself?

778
01:04:16,812 --> 01:04:19,148
- What?
- Did you breast-feed her?

779
01:04:19,231 --> 01:04:21,859
- Now, wait a minute!
- Yes, I did.

780
01:04:22,318 --> 01:04:25,946
- Toughened your nipples, didn't it?
- You son of a bitch!

781
01:04:26,155 --> 01:04:29,742
Amputate a man's leg,
and he can still feel it tickling.

782
01:04:30,159 --> 01:04:33,621
Tell me, Mom,
when your little girl is on the slab,

783
01:04:33,704 --> 01:04:35,706
where will it tickle you?

784
01:04:35,790 --> 01:04:38,751
Take this thing back to Baltimore.

785
01:04:40,294 --> 01:04:43,380
Five-foot-ten, strongly built,
about 180 pounds.

786
01:04:43,506 --> 01:04:45,758
Hair, blond. Eyes, pale blue.

787
01:04:46,258 --> 01:04:47,551
He'd be about 35 now.

788
01:04:47,635 --> 01:04:50,679
He said he lived in Philadelphia,
but may have lied.

789
01:04:50,763 --> 01:04:52,765
That's all I can remember, Mom.

790
01:04:52,848 --> 01:04:55,976
But if I think of any more,
I will let you know.

791
01:04:58,020 --> 01:05:00,439
Oh, and, Senator, just one more thing.

792
01:05:02,775 --> 01:05:04,360
Love your suit.

793
01:05:06,570 --> 01:05:08,781
I tell you now
that in a meeting earlier this evening

794
01:05:08,864 --> 01:05:10,116
with Senator Ruth Martin,

795
01:05:10,199 --> 01:05:13,202
Dr. Lecter agreed
to assist in the investigation

796
01:05:13,285 --> 01:05:16,122
of trying to find the abductor
of Catherine Martin, Buffalo Bill.

797
01:05:16,205 --> 01:05:17,206
How do you fit in, sir?

798
01:05:17,289 --> 01:05:18,791
Well, it's only through
my own unique insight

799
01:05:18,874 --> 01:05:20,918
into Lecter's mind
that this breakthrough was possible.

800
01:05:21,001 --> 01:05:22,086
And Buffalo Bill's real name...

801
01:05:22,169 --> 01:05:26,048
Buffalo Bill's real name is now a matter
of record with the proper authorities.

802
01:05:26,132 --> 01:05:28,717
- Can you give us any more information?
- My name is Dr. Frederick Chilton.

803
01:05:28,801 --> 01:05:30,302
- How do you spell that?
- C-H...

804
01:05:31,887 --> 01:05:36,475
- Are you with Dr. Chilton's group?
- Oh, well, I just saw him outside, sir.

805
01:05:36,851 --> 01:05:40,271
Access to Lecter is strictly limited.
We've been getting death threats.

806
01:05:40,354 --> 01:05:42,064
I understand, sir.

807
01:05:48,112 --> 01:05:50,197
Log in. Check your weapon.

808
01:05:51,031 --> 01:05:53,409
Well, I can't take all the credit for myself.

809
01:05:53,492 --> 01:05:56,036
Senator Martin, the Justice Department,
the people at the FBI,

810
01:05:56,120 --> 01:05:58,330
the folks at the Baltimore State Hospital.

811
01:05:58,414 --> 01:06:01,750
And now for the hard part,
apprehending the suspect.

812
01:06:01,959 --> 01:06:04,420
Excuse me, folks,
I'm gonna have to catch a flight.

813
01:06:08,340 --> 01:06:10,593
Command desk. Officer Jacobs.

814
01:06:19,185 --> 01:06:21,312
Is it true what they're saying?

815
01:06:23,397 --> 01:06:25,441
He's some kind of vampire?

816
01:06:27,776 --> 01:06:30,446
They don't have a name for what he is.

817
01:06:31,113 --> 01:06:32,990
You do know the rules, ma'am?

818
01:06:33,490 --> 01:06:36,118
Yes, Lieutenant Boyle.
I've questioned him before.

819
01:06:39,455 --> 01:06:40,748
Go ahead.

820
01:07:17,660 --> 01:07:19,536
Good evening, Clarice.

821
01:07:21,205 --> 01:07:24,541
I thought you might like
your drawings back, Doctor.

822
01:07:26,669 --> 01:07:28,879
Just until you get your view.

823
01:07:29,380 --> 01:07:31,173
How very thoughtful.

824
01:07:32,591 --> 01:07:35,678
Or did Jack Crawford send you
for one last wheedle

825
01:07:35,761 --> 01:07:38,013
before you're both booted off the case?

826
01:07:38,389 --> 01:07:40,724
No. I came because I wanted to.

827
01:07:45,312 --> 01:07:47,564
People will say we're in love.

828
01:07:51,860 --> 01:07:53,904
Anthrax Island.

829
01:07:54,571 --> 01:07:57,533
That was an especially nice touch, Clarice.

830
01:07:57,741 --> 01:08:00,035
- Yours?
- Yes.

831
01:08:00,911 --> 01:08:04,039
Yeah! That was good.

832
01:08:04,957 --> 01:08:07,001
Pity about poor Catherine, though.

833
01:08:09,545 --> 01:08:12,006
Your anagrams are showing, Doctor.

834
01:08:12,881 --> 01:08:14,383
Louis Friend?

835
01:08:15,134 --> 01:08:18,095
Iron sulfide, also known as Fool's Gold.

836
01:08:18,721 --> 01:08:22,850
Oh, Clarice. Your problem is
you need to get more fun out of life.

837
01:08:23,100 --> 01:08:26,061
You were telling me the truth
back in Baltimore, sir.

838
01:08:26,145 --> 01:08:27,938
Please continue now.

839
01:08:28,230 --> 01:08:31,150
Well, I have read the case files, have you?

840
01:08:31,233 --> 01:08:34,361
Everything you need to find him
is right there in those pages.

841
01:08:34,445 --> 01:08:38,907
- Then tell me how.
- First principles, Clarice. Simplicity.

842
01:08:39,408 --> 01:08:40,909
Read Marcus Aurelius.

843
01:08:40,993 --> 01:08:44,288
Of each particular thing,
ask what is it in itself?

844
01:08:44,496 --> 01:08:46,290
What is its nature?

845
01:08:46,749 --> 01:08:50,002
What does he do, this man you seek?

846
01:08:52,212 --> 01:08:53,714
He kills women.

847
01:08:53,797 --> 01:08:56,342
No! That is incidental.

848
01:08:57,509 --> 01:08:59,345
What is the first
and principal thing he does?

849
01:08:59,428 --> 01:09:02,681
What needs does he serve by killing?

850
01:09:03,223 --> 01:09:04,433
Anger.

851
01:09:06,101 --> 01:09:10,481
Social acceptance
and sexual frustrations...

852
01:09:10,564 --> 01:09:13,484
No! He covets.

853
01:09:14,777 --> 01:09:16,570
That is his nature.

854
01:09:16,904 --> 01:09:19,531
And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?

855
01:09:20,032 --> 01:09:22,368
Do we seek out things to covet?

856
01:09:23,202 --> 01:09:25,245
Make an effort to answer now.

857
01:09:25,329 --> 01:09:27,623
No. We just...

858
01:09:28,040 --> 01:09:31,126
No. We begin by coveting
what we see every day.

859
01:09:31,460 --> 01:09:34,797
Don't you feel eyes
moving over your body, Clarice?

860
01:09:35,631 --> 01:09:38,842
And don't your eyes
seek out the things you want?

861
01:09:39,593 --> 01:09:42,012
All right. Yes. Now please tell me how.

862
01:09:42,388 --> 01:09:46,266
No. It is your turn to tell me, Clarice.

863
01:09:46,475 --> 01:09:49,353
You don't have any more vacations to sell.

864
01:09:49,728 --> 01:09:51,980
Why did you leave that ranch?

865
01:09:52,481 --> 01:09:56,193
Doctor, we don't have anymore time
for any of this now.

866
01:09:56,693 --> 01:09:59,363
But we don't reckon time the same way,
do we, Clarice?

867
01:09:59,446 --> 01:10:01,407
This is all the time you'll ever have.

868
01:10:01,490 --> 01:10:03,909
Later. Now, please, listen to me.
We've only got five...

869
01:10:03,992 --> 01:10:06,578
No! I will listen now.

870
01:10:09,581 --> 01:10:11,417
After your father's murder,
you were orphaned.

871
01:10:11,500 --> 01:10:12,751
You were ten years old.

872
01:10:12,835 --> 01:10:16,588
You went to live with cousins
on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.

873
01:10:16,672 --> 01:10:17,798
And?

874
01:10:19,925 --> 01:10:22,094
And one morning, I just ran away.

875
01:10:22,803 --> 01:10:25,848
Not "just", Clarice. What set you off?

876
01:10:26,640 --> 01:10:30,060
- You started at what time?
- Early. Still dark.

877
01:10:30,436 --> 01:10:34,440
Then something woke you, didn't it?
Was it a dream? What was it?

878
01:10:35,816 --> 01:10:37,818
I heard a strange noise.

879
01:10:38,735 --> 01:10:40,195
What was it?

880
01:10:40,737 --> 01:10:44,241
It was screaming.

881
01:10:46,201 --> 01:10:49,163
Some kind of screaming,
like a child's voice.

882
01:10:49,538 --> 01:10:51,165
What did you do?

883
01:10:51,540 --> 01:10:55,085
I went downstairs, outside.

884
01:10:57,921 --> 01:10:59,965
I crept up into the barn.

885
01:11:00,716 --> 01:11:03,719
I was so scared to look inside, but I had to.

886
01:11:04,928 --> 01:11:08,056
And what did you see, Clarice?
What did you see?

887
01:11:09,808 --> 01:11:13,395
Lambs. They were screaming.

888
01:11:14,521 --> 01:11:17,274
They were slaughtering the spring lambs?

889
01:11:17,691 --> 01:11:19,693
And they were screaming.

890
01:11:20,903 --> 01:11:23,405
- And you ran away?
- No.

891
01:11:24,615 --> 01:11:26,742
First I tried to free them.

892
01:11:27,284 --> 01:11:29,745
I opened the gate to their pen,
but they wouldn't run.

893
01:11:29,828 --> 01:11:33,123
They just stood there, confused.
They wouldn't run.

894
01:11:33,540 --> 01:11:36,210
But you could and you did, didn't you?

895
01:11:36,919 --> 01:11:40,380
Yes. I took one lamb,
and I ran away as fast as I could.

896
01:11:40,464 --> 01:11:43,050
- Where were you going, Clarice?
- I don't know.

897
01:11:43,133 --> 01:11:47,846
I didn't have any food, any water,
and it was very cold, very cold.

898
01:11:50,516 --> 01:11:54,603
I thought if I could save just one, but,

899
01:11:57,147 --> 01:11:58,774
he was so heavy.

900
01:11:59,775 --> 01:12:01,443
He was so heavy.

901
01:12:06,657 --> 01:12:11,036
I didn't get more than a few miles
when the sheriff's car picked me up.

902
01:12:13,789 --> 01:12:15,040
The rancher was so angry,

903
01:12:15,123 --> 01:12:18,627
he sent me to live
at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.

904
01:12:18,710 --> 01:12:20,921
I never saw the ranch again.

905
01:12:21,505 --> 01:12:23,966
What became of your lamb, Clarice?

906
01:12:26,176 --> 01:12:27,803
They killed him.

907
01:12:27,886 --> 01:12:30,264
You still wake up sometimes, don't you?

908
01:12:30,347 --> 01:12:34,935
Wake up in the dark
and hear the screaming of the lambs.

909
01:12:35,978 --> 01:12:37,104
Yes.

910
01:12:38,814 --> 01:12:43,110
And you think if you save poor Catherine,
you could make them stop, don't you?

911
01:12:43,193 --> 01:12:45,571
You think if Catherine lives,

912
01:12:45,654 --> 01:12:48,407
you won't wake up in the dark ever again

913
01:12:48,907 --> 01:12:51,535
to that awful screaming of the lambs.

914
01:12:52,911 --> 01:12:55,872
I don't know. I don't know.

915
01:12:58,083 --> 01:13:01,712
Thank you, Clarice. Thank you.

916
01:13:02,588 --> 01:13:04,631
Tell me his name, Doctor.

917
01:13:11,555 --> 01:13:13,515
Dr. Chilton, I presume.

918
01:13:14,349 --> 01:13:16,518
I think you know each other.

919
01:13:18,186 --> 01:13:19,479
Okay.

920
01:13:20,480 --> 01:13:22,482
- We found her.
- Let's go!

921
01:13:22,733 --> 01:13:24,693
It's your turn, Doctor.

922
01:13:24,901 --> 01:13:26,903
- Out.
- Tell me his name.

923
01:13:26,987 --> 01:13:29,656
Sorry, ma'am, I've got orders.
I have to put you on a plane.

924
01:13:29,740 --> 01:13:31,116
Come on now.

925
01:13:31,199 --> 01:13:32,743
Brave Clarice.

926
01:13:33,410 --> 01:13:37,205
You will let me know when
those lambs stop screaming, won't you?

927
01:13:37,289 --> 01:13:39,291
Tell me his name, Doctor!

928
01:13:39,374 --> 01:13:40,626
Clarice!

929
01:13:41,960 --> 01:13:43,545
Your case file.

930
01:13:48,717 --> 01:13:50,427
Goodbye, Clarice.

931
01:14:56,243 --> 01:14:58,245
Ready when you are, Doc.

932
01:14:58,453 --> 01:15:00,622
Just another minute, please.

933
01:15:09,548 --> 01:15:11,967
The son of a bitch
demanded a second dinner.

934
01:15:12,050 --> 01:15:14,052
Lamb chops, extra rare.

935
01:15:14,136 --> 01:15:16,054
Wonder what he wants for breakfast.

936
01:15:16,138 --> 01:15:18,390
Some damn thing from the zoo?

937
01:15:40,245 --> 01:15:42,038
Good evening, gentlemen.

938
01:15:42,122 --> 01:15:45,625
- Okay, Doc. Grab some floor.
- Same drill as before, please.

939
01:15:53,216 --> 01:15:55,761
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

940
01:16:11,985 --> 01:16:13,111
Okay.

941
01:16:19,993 --> 01:16:21,995
Hand me that, would you?

942
01:16:27,209 --> 01:16:28,376
Thanks.

943
01:16:32,214 --> 01:16:34,299
Mind the drawings, please.

944
01:16:37,385 --> 01:16:38,720
Thank you.

945
01:17:03,078 --> 01:17:05,413
- Jimmy, watch it! He's got me!
- Jesus, Bill!

946
01:17:12,379 --> 01:17:13,880
Jesus Christ!

947
01:18:32,500 --> 01:18:35,086
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

948
01:18:44,346 --> 01:18:46,014
What is this shit?

949
01:18:48,808 --> 01:18:52,520
- Did somebody go up on five?
- No. Nobody went up.

950
01:18:52,854 --> 01:18:54,773
Call Pembry. Ask him...

951
01:18:57,400 --> 01:19:00,153
CP, shots fired on five. Repeat.

952
01:19:00,528 --> 01:19:03,073
- Shots fired on five.
- Sergeant Tate.

953
01:19:05,825 --> 01:19:07,118
Holy shit.

954
01:19:07,202 --> 01:19:09,037
What the hell? Bitch!

955
01:19:09,579 --> 01:19:10,830
Shut up.

956
01:19:11,122 --> 01:19:13,667
- Bobby, get the vest.
- Right, Sarge.

957
01:19:14,334 --> 01:19:16,211
- Brady, Howard...
- Look!

958
01:19:19,339 --> 01:19:20,715
It stopped.

959
01:19:22,217 --> 01:19:23,927
Seal off a 10 block radius.

960
01:19:24,010 --> 01:19:26,805
Get me the SWAT team
and an ambulance double-quick.

961
01:19:26,888 --> 01:19:28,098
We're going up.

962
01:19:57,252 --> 01:19:58,837
Pembry!

963
01:20:00,338 --> 01:20:02,090
Boyle!

964
01:20:14,728 --> 01:20:15,937
Oh, God!

965
01:20:23,236 --> 01:20:24,279
Go.

966
01:20:32,078 --> 01:20:33,538
- Clear!
- Clear!

967
01:20:33,621 --> 01:20:36,583
Command post, two officers down.

968
01:20:36,958 --> 01:20:38,293
- Clear!
- Clear!

969
01:20:39,210 --> 01:20:40,545
Lecter's gone, Sarge.

970
01:20:40,628 --> 01:20:42,464
The prisoner is missing.

971
01:20:42,547 --> 01:20:44,466
Boyle's gun is gone, Sergeant.

972
01:20:44,549 --> 01:20:47,135
Repeat. Lecter is missing and armed.

973
01:20:47,218 --> 01:20:50,263
He stripped the bed.
Might be making a rope.

974
01:20:50,346 --> 01:20:52,015
Check all windows.

975
01:20:52,098 --> 01:20:54,476
Where the fuck is my ambulance?

976
01:20:55,143 --> 01:20:56,519
He's alive.

977
01:20:57,228 --> 01:20:59,314
Sergeant Tate, he's alive!

978
01:20:59,814 --> 01:21:02,942
Get a hold of him where you can
feel his hands, son. Talk to him.

979
01:21:03,485 --> 01:21:04,694
What do I say?

980
01:21:04,778 --> 01:21:07,572
It's Jim Pembry! Now talk to him, damn it!

981
01:21:08,573 --> 01:21:10,700
Lecter is missing and armed.

982
01:21:10,867 --> 01:21:13,119
Pembry. Pembry, can you hear me?

983
01:21:13,203 --> 01:21:16,206
He took Boyle's gun.
Pembry got off one round.

984
01:21:16,289 --> 01:21:18,249
There's a chance Lecter was hit.

985
01:21:18,333 --> 01:21:20,460
Keep breathing in and out. That's it.

986
01:21:20,543 --> 01:21:23,797
You're doing a good job.
You look real good there.

987
01:21:24,547 --> 01:21:27,342
Yeah, you look... You look real good.

988
01:21:44,651 --> 01:21:45,777
- You ready?
- Let's go.

989
01:21:45,860 --> 01:21:47,737
- Let's do it.
- Let's go.

990
01:21:58,832 --> 01:22:01,000
Looking good, Pembry.
You're gonna make it.

991
01:22:01,084 --> 01:22:03,169
You're just fine. You're doing all right.
That's right.

992
01:22:03,253 --> 01:22:05,672
- Okay, I need that IV now.
- Lactated ringers.

993
01:22:05,755 --> 01:22:07,006
Can we get the strap?

994
01:22:07,090 --> 01:22:08,133
Where's the fucking oxygen?

995
01:22:08,216 --> 01:22:09,926
- Looking good, buddy. That's right.
- Bob!

996
01:22:10,009 --> 01:22:11,845
Stay with me. Stay with me here.

997
01:22:13,513 --> 01:22:15,723
